  "response": "Here are the key differences between AT&T DSL and U-verse DSL:\n\nAT&T DSL:\n- Traditional DSL technology\n- Slower speeds (typically up to 6-18 Mbps)\n- Older infrastructure\n- Basic internet service\n- Limited bundling options\n\nAT&T U-verse DSL:\n- Advanced DSL technology\n- Faster speeds (typically up to 45-100 Mbps)\n- Newer infrastructure\n- Integrated TV and phone services\n- More comprehensive bundling options\n- Uses fiber-optic network closer to the home\n- Generally more reliable connection\n- Supports more advanced features like IP-based services\n\nIn essence, U-verse DSL is an upgraded, more modern version of traditional DSL with better performance and more integrated services.",
